<blockquote>
<p><strong>Most advice about E-E-A-T is vague.</strong> It says "build trust." That is unhelpful. The specific implementation — named reviewers, credentialed experts, structured schema, dedicated profile pages, quarterly audits — is what actually moves the trust score. The vagueness is what keeps most sites from acting.</p>
